Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the goodness-of-fit of models, which is a topic in machine learning and statistics, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The use of model classes and the determination of the best-fitting model also suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as a possible sub-category. The paper also involves the computation of various functions, which could fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
